The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Rare film posters light up festival
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                     Rare film posters light up festival
          OUR CORRESPONDENT                          Film personalities Aruna Basudevan from New Delhi and Prabir Mukhmal from Bangladesh inaugurate the festival in Bhubaneswar on Friday evening. Picture by Sanjib Mukherjee                                  
	Bhubaneswar, Dec. 12: A collection of beautiful, old and rare film posters charmed visitors at the third national film festival on art and artists here today.        
	Filmmakers, artists and writers from across the country and abroad attended this thematic annual event touted as the only film festival on art and artists in Asia hosted by the Jatin Das Centre of Art.        
	Representing Indian cinema through different decades of film history, these rare posters collected by the National Film Archive of India would be available for exhibition for another three days.        
	Film posters are a form of art but they are often forgotten, said festival director Bidisha Roy Das.         
	This years festival theme is performing arts, environment with a focus on films on art from Bangladesh.        
	Forty-seven delegates, including Gautam Ghosh, Amol Palekar, Jahnu Barua, Kumar Shahni, Aruna Vasudev, Suresh Kohli and Sunit Tandon are are attending the festival, which features short, documentaries and animation films of Satyajit Ray, Kumar Shahni, Jabbar Patel, Harisadhan Das Gupta, Chidananda Dasgupta, Gulbahar Singh and Madhushree Dutta.                                                                                                                                                                          
